  sodium: 640 mg
---

Preheat #oven to 450 degrees.

Combine @farro{1%cup}, @veggie stock concentrate{2}, and @water{3 1/2%cups} in a
#medium pot{}. Bring to a boil and cook until farro is tender, ~{25-30%minutes}
total.

> TIP: If you end up with any excess stock, simply pour it out. Alternatively,
> if stock evaporates before farro is done, add a splash of water.

Meanwhile, wash and dry all produce. Trim @zucchini{1}; slice into thin rounds.
Cut @roma tomato{1} into 6 wedges (cut both tomatoes for 4 servings). Halve and
peel @red onion{1}; cut one half into ½-inch-thick wedges. Finely chop remaining
half. Dice @fresh mozzarella{4%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Pick @basil{1/2%ounce}
leaves from stems; discard stems. Finely chop half the leaves; tear remaining
leaves into large pieces.

Place onion wedges in the center of a large piece of #foil. Lift up and crimp
sides of foil to make a bowl. Pour in half the @balsamic vinegar{5%teaspoon}
(you'll use the rest later) and a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon}. Season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Place on one side of a #baking sheet{}.

On opposite side of baking sheet, toss tomato and zucchini with a drizzle of
@olive oil{}, @Italian seasoning{1%teaspoon}, salt, and pepper (use 2 baking
sheets for 4 servings). Roast until tomato and zucchini are browned and onion
wedges are softened, ~{15-20%minutes}. Meanwhile, heat a #small pan{} over
medium-high heat. Add @almonds{1%ounce} and toast, stirring often, until
fragrant and lightly browned, ~{3-4%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a
#small bowl{}.

In a second small bowl, whisk together remaining vinegar and a large drizzle of
@olive oil{}. Season with salt and pepper. Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%teaspoon}
in same pan used to toast almonds over medium-high heat. Add chopped onion and
cook until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

Stir chopped onion, chopped basil, half the mozzarella, and @butter{1%tablespoon}
into farro. Season with salt and pepper; divide between bowls. Top with roasted
veggies and remaining mozzarella. Drizzle with vinaigrette and sprinkle with
almonds and torn basil.

> If making for 4 servings, double the farro, stock concentrates, water, and use
> 2 baking sheets. Use 2 TBSP butter instead of 1.